qbAtmMIB.name: qbAtmMIB
qbAtmMIB.description: This module defines additional objects for management of ATM links in Quantum Bridge devices, above and beyond what is defined in the standard ATM mib, and proposed drafts.

QbAtmPnniWeight.name: QbAtmPnniWeight
QbAtmPnniWeight.description: The ATM administrative weight of the ATM interface used by the PNNI Routing Control

QbAtmPnniNodeId.name: QbAtmPnniNodeId
QbAtmPnniNodeId.description: Global PNNI Node Id used in the QB PNNI system.

QbAtmPnniHelloState.name: QbAtmPnniHelloState
QbAtmPnniHelloState.description: The state of an instance of the PNNI Hello State machine.

QbAtmPnniAtmAddr.name: QbAtmPnniAtmAddr
QbAtmPnniAtmAddr.description: The ATM address used by the network entity. The address types are: no address (0 octets), and NSAP (20 octets).

QbAtmPnniNodeIndex.name: QbAtmPnniNodeIndex
QbAtmPnniNodeIndex.description: An index that identifies a logical PNNI entity within the managed system. The distinguished value zero indicates the null instance or no instance in the qbAtmPnniNodeCfgParentNodeIndex. In all other cases, the distinguished value zero indicates a logical entity within the switching system that manages routes only over non-PNNI interfaces. By default, only the node identified by node index one is created, and all PNNI interfaces are associated with that node.

qbAtmF4F5LLID.name: qbAtmF4F5LLID
qbAtmF4F5LLID.description: This object stores Loopback Location ID (LLID).

qbAtmDefaultPCBE.name: qbAtmDefaultPCBE
qbAtmDefaultPCBE.description: This object stores the default atm cell tax to be used by the system.

qbAtmInterfaceConfTable.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfTable
qbAtmInterfaceConfTable.description: The Quantum Bridge ATM Interface Configuration Table contains extensions to the ATM Interface Configuration Table, one entry per ATM interface.

qbAtmInterfaceConfEntry.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfEntry
qbAtmInterfaceConfEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum ATM Interface Configuration Table. Every ATM interface contains a corresponding entry in the table.

qbAtmInterfaceConfPolicingStatus.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfPolicingStatus
qbAtmInterfaceConfPolicingStatus.description: If this object is set to 'enable' the policing is enabled on this interface. If the object set to 'disable,' the policing is disabled. Note: policing can be set on the S622 and 155 cards only.

qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvcVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvcVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvcVpi.description: This object indicates the maximum value of VPI that can be used to create a VC on a given ATM native interface.

qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvcVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvcVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvcVpi.description: This object indicates the minimum value of VPI that can be used to create a VC on a given ATM native interface.

qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvcVci.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvcVci
qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvcVci.description: This object indicates the maximum value of VCI that can be used to create a VC on a given ATM native interface.

qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvcVci.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvcVci
qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvcVci.description: This object indicates the minimum value of VCI that can be used to create a VC on a given ATM native interface.

qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvpVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvpVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfMaxPvpVpi.description: This object indicates the maximum value of VPI that can be used to create a VP on a given ATM native interface.

qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvpVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvpVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfMinPvpVpi.description: This object indicates the minimum value of VPI that can be used to create a VP on a given ATM native interface.

qbAtmTrafficDescrParamTable.name: qbAtmTrafficDescrParamTable
qbAtmTrafficDescrParamTable.description: The Quantum Bridge ATM Traffic Descriptor Table contains extensions to the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table.

qbAtmTrafficDescrParamEntry.name: qbAtmTrafficDescrParamEntry
qbAtmTrafficDescrParamEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum Bridge ATM Traffic Descriptor Table.

qbAtmTrafficDescrParamName.name: qbAtmTrafficDescrParamName
qbAtmTrafficDescrParamName.description: A textual description of the traffic descriptor.

qbAtmTrafficDescrParamDefault.name: qbAtmTrafficDescrParamDefault
qbAtmTrafficDescrParamDefault.description: The object indicates whether or not this is a default traffic descriptor. Traffic descriptor with indexes from 1 to 20 are default traffic descriptors and cannot be deleted.

qbAtmVclTable.name: qbAtmVclTable
qbAtmVclTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Table contains an extension to the atmVclConnectTable, An entry in this table models VCLs.

qbAtmVclEntry.name: qbAtmVclEntry
qbAtmVclEntry.description: An entry in the QB ATM atmVclConnectTable.

qbAtmVclLoopback.name: qbAtmVclLoopback
qbAtmVclLoopback.description: Enable loopback on this ATM VCL

qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackInsert.name: qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackInsert
qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackInsert.description: This is a loopback Insert object for LLID. Start loopback Insert by setting this to an LLID value.

qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackStatus.name: qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackStatus
qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackStatus.description: Status of loopback Insert command: in-progress, success, timeout.

qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackTimestamp.name: qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackTimestamp
qbAtmVclF4F5LoopbackTimestamp.description: Value of sysUptime when last Insert completed.

qbAtmVclMgmtIpAddr.name: qbAtmVclMgmtIpAddr
qbAtmVclMgmtIpAddr.description: Active IP Address for in-band Management SNMP of this chassis.

qbAtmVclMgmtIpMask.name: qbAtmVclMgmtIpMask
qbAtmVclMgmtIpMask.description: This is the IP network mask associated with the in-band Management interface.

qbAtmVclMgmtNeighborIP.name: qbAtmVclMgmtNeighborIP
qbAtmVclMgmtNeighborIP.description: This is the neighbor IP address associated with the in-band Management interface.

qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus.name: qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus
qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus.description: The transmitted OAM status for the PVC.

qbAtmVclF4F5TxLastChange.name: qbAtmVclF4F5TxLastChange
qbAtmVclF4F5TxLastChange.description: The value of sysUPtime when qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus last changed.

qbAtmVclF4F5RxStatus.name: qbAtmVclF4F5RxStatus
qbAtmVclF4F5RxStatus.description: The received OAM status of the PVC.

qbAtmVclF4F5RxLastChange.name: qbAtmVclF4F5RxLastChange
qbAtmVclF4F5RxLastChange.description: The value of sysUPtime when qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus last changed.

qbAtmVplTable.name: qbAtmVplTable
qbAtmVplTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Table contains an extension to the atmVclConnectTable, An entry in this table models VPLs.

qbAtmVplEntry.name: qbAtmVplEntry
qbAtmVplEntry.description: An entry in the QB ATM qbAtmVpTable.

qbAtmVplLoopback.name: qbAtmVplLoopback
qbAtmVplLoopback.description: Enable loopback on this ATM VPL

qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackInsert.name: qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackInsert
qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackInsert.description: This is a loopback Insert object for LLID. Start loopback Insert by setting this to an LLID value.

qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackStatus.name: qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackStatus
qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackStatus.description: Status of loopback Insert command: in-progress, success, timeout.

qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackTimestamp.name: qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackTimestamp
qbAtmVplF4F5LoopbackTimestamp.description: Value of sysUptime when last Insert completed.

qbAtmVplF4F5TxStatus.name: qbAtmVplF4F5TxStatus
qbAtmVplF4F5TxStatus.description: The transmitted OAM status for the PVP.

qbAtmVplF4F5TxLastChange.name: qbAtmVplF4F5TxLastChange
qbAtmVplF4F5TxLastChange.description: The value of sysUPtime when qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus last changed.

qbAtmVplF4F5RxStatus.name: qbAtmVplF4F5RxStatus
qbAtmVplF4F5RxStatus.description: The received OAM status of the PVP.

qbAtmVplF4F5RxLastChange.name: qbAtmVplF4F5RxLastChange
qbAtmVplF4F5RxLastChange.description: The value of sysUPtime when qbAtmVclF4F5TxStatus last changed.

qbAtmVcCrossConnectTable.name: qbAtmVcCrossConnectTable
qbAtmVcCrossConnectTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Table contains an extension to the atmVcCrossConnectTable, An entry in this table models two cross-connected VCLs.

qbAtmVcCrossConnectEntry.name: qbAtmVcCrossConnectEntry
qbAtmVcCrossConnectEntry.description: An entry in the QB ATM atmVcCrossConnectTable.

qbAtmVcCrossConnectName.name: qbAtmVcCrossConnectName
qbAtmVcCrossConnectName.description: A textual description for the cross connect.

qbAtmVcCrossConnectRxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbAtmVcCrossConnectRxTrafficDescrIndex
qbAtmVcCrossConnectRxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this VCLs cross-connect.

qbAtmVcCrossConnectTxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbAtmVcCrossConnectTxTrafficDescrIndex
qbAtmVcCrossConnectTxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this VCLs cross-connect

qbAtmVpCrossConnectTable.name: qbAtmVpCrossConnectTable
qbAtmVpCrossConnectTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Table contains an extension to the atmVpCrossConnectTable, An entry in this table models two cross-connected VPLs.

qbAtmVpCrossConnectEntry.name: qbAtmVpCrossConnectEntry
qbAtmVpCrossConnectEntry.description: An entry in the QB ATM atmVpCrossConnectTable.

qbAtmVpCrossConnectName.name: qbAtmVpCrossConnectName
qbAtmVpCrossConnectName.description: A textual description for the cross connect.

qbAtmVpCrossConnectRxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbAtmVpCrossConnectRxTrafficDescrIndex
qbAtmVpCrossConnectRxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this VPLs cross-connect.

qbAtmVpCrossConnectTxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbAtmVpCrossConnectTxTrafficDescrIndex
qbAtmVpCrossConnectTxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this VPLs cross-connect

qbAtmPnniNodeTable.name: qbAtmPnniNodeTable
qbAtmPnniNodeTable.description: The QbAtmpnniNodeTable contains attributes that affect the operation of a PNNI logical node. There is a single row in this table for each PNNI peer group that the managed system is expected or eligible to become a member of.

qbAtmPnniNodeEntry.name: qbAtmPnniNodeEntry
qbAtmPnniNodeEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a PNNI logical node in this switching system.

qbAtmPnniNodeIndex.name: qbAtmPnniNodeIndex
qbAtmPnniNodeIndex.description: A value assigned to a node in this switching system that uniquely identifies it in the MIB.

qbAtmPnniNodeNetAddrPrefix.name: qbAtmPnniNodeNetAddrPrefix
qbAtmPnniNodeNetAddrPrefix.description: Indicates the Network Prefix to use for the ATM End System Address. The value is 13 bytes long, and is specified in the hexadecimal format. If less than 13 bytes(26 chars) are received, the agent appends trailing zero's. The object can be set to ''h, if PNNI protocol is desirable on all interfaces.

qbAtmPnniNodeEndSysId.name: qbAtmPnniNodeEndSysId
qbAtmPnniNodeEndSysId.description: Indicates the End System Identifier for ATM End System Address. The value is 7 bytes long, and is specified in the hexadecimal format. The object can be set to ''h, if PNNI protocol is desirable on all interfaces.

qbAtmPnniNodeLevel.name: qbAtmPnniNodeLevel
qbAtmPnniNodeLevel.description: The level of PNNI hierarchy at which this node exists. This attribute is used to determine the default node ID and the default peer group ID for this node. This object may only be written when pnniNodeAdminStatus has the value down.

qbAtmPnniNodeRowStatus.name: qbAtmPnniNodeRowStatus
qbAtmPnniNodeRowStatus.description: To create, delete, activate and de-activate a Node. Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the corresponding row to be created. Setting this object to destroy(6) causes the corresponding row to be deleted. Note that -- currently-- only a single instance of a row can be created in this table.

qbAtmPnniNodeOperStatus.name: qbAtmPnniNodeOperStatus
qbAtmPnniNodeOperStatus.description: Indicates the Operational Status of the PNNI Node. For Logical Group Nodes, the Operational Status will be up only if the child becomes the PGL.

qbAtmPnniNodeAtmAddress.name: qbAtmPnniNodeAtmAddress
qbAtmPnniNodeAtmAddress.description: This node's ATM End System Address. Remote systems wishing to exchange PNNI protocol packets with this node should direct packets or calls to this address. The current Qb implementation does not support writing this value.

qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupId.name: qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupId
qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupId.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Section 5.3.2, Annex F
qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupId.description: The Peer Group Identifier of the peer group that the given node is to become a member of.

qbAtmPnniIfTable.name: qbAtmPnniIfTable
qbAtmPnniIfTable.description: The qbAtmPnniIfTable contains the attributes necessary to configure a physical interface on a switching system capable of being used for PNNI routing. An ifIndex is used as the instance ID to uniquely identify the interface on the local switching system. This index has the same value as the ifIndex object defined in RFC 1573 for the same interface, since this table correlates with the ifTable in RFC 1573. One row in this table is created by the managed system for each row in the ifTable that has an ifType of atm(37) or atmLogical(80).

qbAtmPnniIfEntry.name: qbAtmPnniIfEntry
qbAtmPnniIfEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing PNNI specific interface information in this switching system.

qbAtmPnniIfNodeIndex.name: qbAtmPnniIfNodeIndex
qbAtmPnniIfNodeIndex.description: Identifies the node within the switching system that the interface is directly attached to. Note: For this release this value can be set only to 1.

qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightCbr.name: qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightCbr
qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightCbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the constant bit rate service category.

qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightRtVbr.name: qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightRtVbr
qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightRtVbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the real-time variable bit rate service category.

qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightNrtVbr.name: qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightNrtVbr
qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightNrtVbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the non-real-time variable bit rate service category.

qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightAbr.name: qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightAbr
qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightAbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the available bit rate service category.

qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightUbr.name: qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightUbr
qbAtmPnniIfAdmWeightUbr.description: The administrative weight of this interface for the unspecified bit rate service category.

qbAtmPnniIfRccServiceCategory.name: qbAtmPnniIfRccServiceCategory
qbAtmPnniIfRccServiceCategory.description: The service category used for the PNNI routing control channel (VCI=18) on this interface.

qbAtmPnniIfRccTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbAtmPnniIfRccTrafficDescrIndex
qbAtmPnniIfRccTrafficDescrIndex.description: The traffic descriptor index referring to the entry in the atmTrafficDescrParamTable defined in RFC 1695 that specifies the traffic allocation for the PNNI routing control channel (VCI=18) on this interface.

qbAtmPnniIfPolicingStatus.name: qbAtmPnniIfPolicingStatus
qbAtmPnniIfPolicingStatus.description: If this object is set to enable, the policing is enabled on this interface. If the object is set to 'disable' the policing is disabled.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrTable.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrTable
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrTable.description: A table containing all the attributes necessary to determine what the PNNI entity believes is reachable in terms of ATM End System Addresses, and to determine which nodes are advertising this reachability. This table is also used to configure static routes to reachable address prefixes. The local node index that receives the reachability information, reachable address, address prefix length, and an index that distinguishes between multiple listings of connectivity to a given address prefix from a given local node are combined to form an instance ID for this object.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrEntry.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrEntry
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a reachable address prefix.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrIfIndex.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrIfIndex
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrIfIndex.description: The local interface over which the reachable address can be reached.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrAddress.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrAddress
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrAddress.description: The value of the ATM End System Address prefix.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrPrefixLength.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrPrefixLength
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrPrefixLength.description: Indicates the number of bits to be applied to the ATM End System Address prefix.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrRowStatus.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrRowStatus
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrRowStatus.description: To create, delete, activate and de-activate a reachable address prefix.

qbAtmPnniRouteAddrProto.name: qbAtmPnniRouteAddrProto
qbAtmPnniRouteAddrProto.description: This object indicates the Routing mechanism through which the connectivity from the advertising node to the reachable address prefix was learned.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigTable.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigTable
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigTable.description: This table contains ATM local interface configuration parameters, one entry per ATM interface port.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigEntry.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigEntry
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigEntry.description: This list contains additonal ATM interface configuration parameters and state variables.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigMode.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigMode
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigMode.description: The type of ATM interface which is either a UNI (User to Network), PNNI or IISP. To modify the qbAtmInterfaceConfSignType, ifAdminStatus has to be down.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSide.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSide
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSide.description: The side of ATM interface which is either a user or network side. NotApplicable value implies that qbAtmInterfaceConfSignType is other than uni or iisp.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigParseMode.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigParseMode
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigParseMode.description: Indicates to the signalling stack to use strict parsing of the INformation Elements (IEs) within signalling messages. This parameter is set to 'on' for conformance testing. For systems that do not test conformance it is recommended to set the object to 'off'.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigAdminStatus.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigAdminStatus
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigAdminStatus.description: Enable/Disable signalling/sscop on this interface. To modify the qbAtmInterfaceConfSignAdminStatus, ifAdminStatus has to be down.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMinVci.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMinVci
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMinVci.description: The minimum value of SVC connection for vci.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMaxVci.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMaxVci
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMaxVci.description: The maximum value of SVC connection for vci.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMinVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMinVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMinVpi.description: The minimum value of SVC connection for vpi.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMaxVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMaxVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvcMaxVpi.description: The maximum value of SVC connection for vpi.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvpMinVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvpMinVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvpMinVpi.description: The minimum value of SVP connection for vpi.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvpMaxVpi.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvpMaxVpi
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigSvpMaxVpi.description: The maximum value of SVP connection for vpi.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigLastChange.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigLastChange
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this interface changed its current administrative state.

qbAtmInterfaceConfSigIlmiEnable.name: qbAtmInterfaceConfSigIlmiEnable
qbAtmInterfaceConfSigIlmiEnable.description: Can be enabled only if signaling is configured. ILMI is enabled by default when signaling is configured on the system and the user may enter the disable option .

qbAtmPnniNbrPeerTable.name: qbAtmPnniNbrPeerTable
qbAtmPnniNbrPeerTable.description: The qbAtmPnniNbrPeer Object contains all the attributes necessary to describe the relationship a node in this switching system has with a neighboring node within the same peer group. A concatenation of the Node Identifier of the node within the local switching system and the neighboring peer's Node Identifier is used to form the instance ID for this object. The entire qbAtmPnniNbrPeer object is read-only, reflecting the fact that neighboring peers are discovered dynamically by the PNNI protocol rather than configured.

qbAtmPnniNbrPeerEntry.name: qbAtmPnniNbrPeerEntry
qbAtmPnniNbrPeerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about this node's relationship with a neighboring peer node.

qbAtmPnniPeerRemoteNodeId.name: qbAtmPnniPeerRemoteNodeId
qbAtmPnniPeerRemoteNodeId.description: The Node Identifier of the neighboring peer node.

qbAtmPnniPeerState.name: qbAtmPnniPeerState
qbAtmPnniPeerState.description: Indicates the state of this node's Neighboring Peer State Machine associated with qbAtmPnniPeerRemoteNodeId.

qbAtmPnniPeerSvccRccIndex.name: qbAtmPnniPeerSvccRccIndex
qbAtmPnniPeerSvccRccIndex.description: Identifies the SVCC-based RCC being used to communicate with the neighboring peer if one exists. If both the local node and the neighboring peer node are lowest-level nodes, this attribute is set to zero.

qbAtmPnniPeerPortCount.name: qbAtmPnniPeerPortCount
qbAtmPnniPeerPortCount.description: A count of the total number of ports that connect to the neighboring peer. If the neighboring peer only communicates via an SVCC-based RCC, the value of this attribute is set to zero. Otherwise it is set to the total number of ports to the neighboring peer in the Hello state 2-WayInside.

qbAtmPnniPeerRcvDbSums.name: qbAtmPnniPeerRcvDbSums
qbAtmPnniPeerRcvDbSums.description: A count of the number of Database Summary Packets received from the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerXmtDbSums.name: qbAtmPnniPeerXmtDbSums
qbAtmPnniPeerXmtDbSums.description: A count of the number of Database Summary Packets transmitted to the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtsps.name: qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtsps
qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtsps.description: A count of the number of PTSPs received from the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtsps.name: qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtsps
qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtsps.description: A count of the number of PTSPs (re)transmitted to the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtseReqs.name: qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtseReqs
qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtseReqs.description: A count of the number of PTSE Request packets received from the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtseReqs.name: qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtseReqs
qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtseReqs.description: A count of the number of PTSE Request packets transmitted to the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtseAcks.name: qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtseAcks
qbAtmPnniPeerRcvPtseAcks.description: A count of the number of PTSE Ack packets received from the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtseAcks.name: qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtseAcks
qbAtmPnniPeerXmtPtseAcks.description: A count of the number of PTSE Ack packets transmitted to the neighboring peer.

qbAtmPnniNodePglTable.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglTable
qbAtmPnniNodePglTable.description: Peer group leader election information for a PNNI node in this switching system.

qbAtmPnniNodePglEntry.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglEntry
qbAtmPnniNodePglEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing PGL election information of a PNNI logical node in this switching system.

qbAtmPnniNodePglLeadershipPriority.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglLeadershipPriority
qbAtmPnniNodePglLeadershipPriority.description: The Leadership priority value this node should advertise in its nodal information group for the given peer group. Only the value zero can be used with nodes that are not PGL/LGN capable. If there is no configured parent node index or no corresponding entry in the pnniNodeTable, then the advertised leadership priority is zero regardless of this value.

qbAtmPnniNodeCfgParentNodeIndex.name: qbAtmPnniNodeCfgParentNodeIndex
qbAtmPnniNodeCfgParentNodeIndex.description: The local node index used to identify the node that will represent this peer group at the next higher level of hierarchy, if this node becomes peer group leader. The value 0 indicates that there is no parent node.

qbAtmPnniNodePglInitTime.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglInitTime
qbAtmPnniNodePglInitTime.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G PGLInitTime
qbAtmPnniNodePglInitTime.description: The amount of time in seconds this node will delay advertising its choice of preferred PGL after having initialized operation and reached the full state with at least one neighbor in the peer group.

qbAtmPnniNodePglOverrideDelay.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglOverrideDelay
qbAtmPnniNodePglOverrideDelay.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G OverrideDelay
qbAtmPnniNodePglOverrideDelay.description: The amount of time in seconds a node will wait for itself to be declared the preferred PGL by unanimous agreement among its peers. In the absence of unanimous agreement this will be the amount of time that will pass before this node considers a two thirds majority as sufficient agreement to declare itself peer group leader, abandoning the attempt to get unanimous agreement.

qbAtmPnniNodePglReelectTime.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglReelectTime
qbAtmPnniNodePglReelectTime.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G ReElectionInterval
qbAtmPnniNodePglReelectTime.description: The amount of time in seconds after losing connectivity to the current peer group leader, that this node will wait before re-starting the process of electing a new peer group leader.

qbAtmPnniNodePglState.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglState
qbAtmPnniNodePglState.description: Indicates the state that this node is in with respect to the Peer Group Leader election that takes place in the node's peer group. The values are enumerated in the Peer Group Leader State Machine.

qbAtmPnniNodePreferredPgl.name: qbAtmPnniNodePreferredPgl
qbAtmPnniNodePreferredPgl.description: The Node ID of the node which the local node believes should be or become the peer group leader. This is also the value the local node is currently advertising in the `Preferred Peer Group Leader Node ID' field of its nodal information group within the given peer group. If a Preferred PGL has not been chosen, this attribute's value is set to (all) zero(s).

qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupLeader.name: qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupLeader
qbAtmPnniNodePeerGroupLeader.description: The Node Identifier of the node which is currently operating as peer group leader of the peer group this node belongs to. If a PGL has not been elected, this attribute's value is set to (all) zero(s).

qbAtmPnniNodePglTimeStamp.name: qbAtmPnniNodePglTimeStamp
qbAtmPnniNodePglTimeStamp.description: The time at which the current Peer Group Leader established itself.

qbAtmPnniNodeActiveParentNodeId.name: qbAtmPnniNodeActiveParentNodeId
qbAtmPnniNodeActiveParentNodeId.description: The Node Identifier value being used by the Peer Group Leader to represent this peer group at the next higher level of the hierarchy. If this node is at the highest level of the hierarchy or if no PGL has yet been elected the PNNI Protocol Entity sets the value of this attribute to (all) zero(s).

qbAtmPnniNodeTimerTable.name: qbAtmPnniNodeTimerTable
qbAtmPnniNodeTimerTable.description: A table of initial PNNI timer values and significant change thresholds.

qbAtmPnniNodeTimerEntry.name: qbAtmPnniNodeTimerEntry
qbAtmPnniNodeTimerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing initial PNNI timer values and significant change thresholds of a PNNI logical node in this switching system.

qbAtmPnniNodePtseHolddown.name: qbAtmPnniNodePtseHolddown
qbAtmPnniNodePtseHolddown.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G MinPTSEInterval
qbAtmPnniNodePtseHolddown.description: The initial value for the PTSE hold down timer that will be used by the given node to limit the rate at which it can re-originate PTSEs. It must be a positive non-zero number.

qbAtmPnniNodeHelloHolddown.name: qbAtmPnniNodeHelloHolddown
qbAtmPnniNodeHelloHolddown.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G MinHelloInterval
qbAtmPnniNodeHelloHolddown.description: The initial value for the Hello hold down timer that will be used by the given node to limit the rate at which it sends Hellos. It must be a positive non-zero number.

qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInterval.name: qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInterval
qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInterval.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G HelloInterval
qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInterval.description: The initial value for the Hello Timer. In the absence of triggered Hellos, this node will send one Hello packet on each of its ports on this interval.

qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInactivityFactor.name: qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInactivityFactor
qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInactivityFactor.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G InactivityFactor
qbAtmPnniNodeHelloInactivityFactor.description: The value for the Hello Inactivity factor that this node will use to determine when a neighbor has gone down.

qbAtmPnniNodeHlinkInact.name: qbAtmPnniNodeHlinkInact
qbAtmPnniNodeHlinkInact.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G HorizontalLinkInactivityTime
qbAtmPnniNodeHlinkInact.description: The amount of time a node will continue to advertise a horizontal (logical) link for which it has not received and processed a LGN Horizontal Link information group.

qbAtmPnniNodePtseRefreshInterval.name: qbAtmPnniNodePtseRefreshInterval
qbAtmPnniNodePtseRefreshInterval.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G PTSERefreshInterval
qbAtmPnniNodePtseRefreshInterval.description: The initial value for the Refresh timer that this node will use to drive (re-)origination of PTSEs in the absence of triggered updates.

qbAtmPnniNodePtseLifetimeFactor.name: qbAtmPnniNodePtseLifetimeFactor
qbAtmPnniNodePtseLifetimeFactor.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G PTSELifetimeFactor
qbAtmPnniNodePtseLifetimeFactor.description: The value for the lifetime multiplier, expressed as a percentage. The result of multiplying the qbAtmPnniNodePtseRefreshInterval attribute value by this attribute value is used as the initial lifetime that this node places into self-originated PTSEs.

qbAtmPnniNodeRxmtInterval.name: qbAtmPnniNodeRxmtInterval
qbAtmPnniNodeRxmtInterval.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G DSRxmtInterval, RequestRxmtInterval, PTSERetransmissionInterval
qbAtmPnniNodeRxmtInterval.description: The period between retransmissions of unacknowledged Database Summary packets, PTSE Request packets, and PTSPs.

qbAtmPnniNodePeerDelayedAckInterval.name: qbAtmPnniNodePeerDelayedAckInterval
qbAtmPnniNodePeerDelayedAckInterval.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Annex G PeerDelayedAckInterval, Appendix G
qbAtmPnniNodePeerDelayedAckInterval.description: The minimum amount of time between transmissions of delayed PTSE acknowledgement packets.

qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrPm.name: qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrPm
qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrPm.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Section 5.8.5.2.5.4, Annex G AvCR_PM
qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrPm.description: The proportional multiplier used in the algorithms that determine significant change for AvCR parameters, expressed as a percentage.

qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrMt.name: qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrMt
qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrMt.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Section 5.8.5.2.5.4, Annex G AvCR_mT
qbAtmPnniNodeAvcrMt.description: The minimum threshold used in the algorithms that determine significant change for AvCR parameters, expressed as a percentage.

qbAtmPnniNodeCdvPm.name: qbAtmPnniNodeCdvPm
qbAtmPnniNodeCdvPm.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Section 5.8.5.2.5.6, Annex G CDV_PM
qbAtmPnniNodeCdvPm.description: The proportional multiplier used in the algorithms that determine significant change for CDV metrics, expressed as a percentage.

qbAtmPnniNodeCtdPm.name: qbAtmPnniNodeCtdPm
qbAtmPnniNodeCtdPm.reference: ATM Forum PNNI 1.0 Section 5.8.5.2.5.5, Annex G maxCTD_PM
qbAtmPnniNodeCtdPm.description: The proportional multiplier used in the algorithms that determine significant change for CTD metrics, expressed as a percentage.

qbAtmPnniLinkTable.name: qbAtmPnniLinkTable
qbAtmPnniLinkTable.description: This table contains the attributes necessary to describe the operation of logical links attached to the local switching system and the relationship with the neighbor nodes on the other end of the links. Links are attached to a specific node within the switching system. A concatenation of the Node Index of the node within the local switching system and the port ID are used as the instance ID to uniquely identify the link. Links may represent horizontal links between lowest level neighboring peers, outside links, uplinks, or horizontal links to/from LGNs. The entire qbAtmPnniLink object is read-only, reflecting the fact that this information is discovered dynamically by the PNNI protocol rather than configured.

qbAtmPnniLinkEntry.name: qbAtmPnniLinkEntry
qbAtmPnniLinkEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a link attached to a PNNI logical node in this switching system.

qbAtmPnniLinkPortId.name: qbAtmPnniLinkPortId
qbAtmPnniLinkPortId.description: The Port Identifier of the link as selected by the local node. This value has meaning only within the context of the node to which the port is attached.

qbAtmPnniLinkType.name: qbAtmPnniLinkType
qbAtmPnniLinkType.description: Indicates the type of link being described.

qbAtmPnniLinkHelloState.name: qbAtmPnniLinkHelloState
qbAtmPnniLinkHelloState.description: For horizontal and outside links between lowest-level nodes and for links of unknown type, this attribute indicates the state of the Hello protocol exchange over this link. For links to/from LGNs, this attribute indicates the state of the corresponding LGN Horizontal Link Hello State Machine. For uplinks (where the port ID is not also used for the underlying outside link), this attribute is set to notApplicable.

qbAtmHiddenVclTable.name: qbAtmHiddenVclTable
qbAtmHiddenVclTable.description: The QB table with extensions to atmVclTable

qbAtmHiddenVclName.name: qbAtmHiddenVclName
qbAtmHiddenVclName.description: A textual description for the SPVC name.

qbAtmHiddenVclType.name: qbAtmHiddenVclType
qbAtmHiddenVclType.description: Value for the interface type. Native ATM - Q155, S622; non-native - E1, DS1, ENET, VT

qbAtmHiddenVclIfIndex.name: qbAtmHiddenVclIfIndex
qbAtmHiddenVclIfIndex.description: ifIndex value for IOT interface. This value is not used for native ATM interfaces.

qbAtmHiddenVclVtIndex.name: qbAtmHiddenVclVtIndex
qbAtmHiddenVclVtIndex.description: Address information for a VT card. This value is used for VT cards only.

qbAtmStatsBuffOverCells.name: qbAtmStatsBuffOverCells
qbAtmStatsBuffOverCells.description: This object gives the number of cells discarded due to buffer overflows.

qbAtmStatsInvalidCells.name: qbAtmStatsInvalidCells
qbAtmStatsInvalidCells.description: This object gives the number of cells discarded due to unknown VPI/VCI.

qbAtmStatsInvUpdateCells.name: qbAtmStatsInvUpdateCells
qbAtmStatsInvUpdateCells.description: This object gives the number of cells discarded due to internal switch errors.

qbAtmInterfaceStatTable.name: qbAtmInterfaceStatTable
qbAtmInterfaceStatTable.description: The Quantum Bridge ATM Interface Statistic Table contains ATM layer statistics for each ATM interface.

qbAtmInterfaceStatEntry.name: qbAtmInterfaceStatEntry
qbAtmInterfaceStatEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum ATM Interface Table. Every ATM interface contains a corresponding entry in the table.

qbAtmInterfaceStatTxOAMCells.name: qbAtmInterfaceStatTxOAMCells
qbAtmInterfaceStatTxOAMCells.description: The total number of valid OAM cells transmitted by this atm layer interface.

qbAtmInterfaceStatRxOAMCells.name: qbAtmInterfaceStatRxOAMCells
qbAtmInterfaceStatRxOAMCells.description: The total number of OAS ATM cells received by this atm layer interface.

qbAtmInBandMgtTable.name: qbAtmInBandMgtTable
qbAtmInBandMgtTable.description: The QbAtmInBandMgtTable defines in-band Management IP channels for use by ATM connections.

qbAtmPkt.name: qbAtmPkt
qbAtmPkt.description: This traffic descriptor type is to define a connection with an Ethernet endpoint, and it is for a user that does not want to use ATM parameters directly. The EtherNet bandwidth will be converted to a nrtVbr traffic descriptor. The conversion from Ethernet bandwidth to ATM cell rate must add an ATM cell tax. This is defined using the pcbe (packet-to-cell bandwidth expansion) factor. If this is not defined for the traffic descriptor, then the system default (qbAtmDefaultPCBE)should be used. The use of the parameter vector for this type: Parameter 1: minbw, the minimum guarnteed bandwidth fo rthe connection. This is defined in Mb/sec. (0-100). Parameter 2: maxbw, the maximum bursting capability of the connection. This is defined in Mb/sec (1-100). It is default to minbw. Parameter 3: bw, indicates the bandwidth for the PON segment. Vaules are expressed in Mb, and may take interger value between 1 and 100. (only apply to 155Mb PON). It is default to minbw. Parameter 4: pcbe, it defines the packed-to-cell bandwidth expansion. This is the percentage overhead that is used to convert Ethernet bandwidth to ATM cell rates. It is default to qbAtmDefaultPCBE. Parameter 5: not used.

qbAtmInBandMgtEntry.name: qbAtmInBandMgtEntry
qbAtmInBandMgtEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about an in-band Management channel.

qbAtmInBandMgtIpAddr.name: qbAtmInBandMgtIpAddr
qbAtmInBandMgtIpAddr.description: An IP Address for in-band SNMP Management of this chassis.

qbAtmInBandMgtIpMask.name: qbAtmInBandMgtIpMask
qbAtmInBandMgtIpMask.description: The IP Network Mask associated with this in-band SNMP Management IP Address.

qbAtmInBandMgtIpIfIndex.name: qbAtmInBandMgtIpIfIndex
qbAtmInBandMgtIpIfIndex.description: The Interface associated with this in-band management address.

qbAtmInBandMgtNeighborIp.name: qbAtmInBandMgtNeighborIp
qbAtmInBandMgtNeighborIp.description: This is the neighbor IP address associated with the in-band Management Interface. If the qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is any value other than pvc(1), this object is non-applicable.

qbAtmInBandMgtIfIndex.name: qbAtmInBandMgtIfIndex
qbAtmInBandMgtIfIndex.description: This is the interface index associated with the in-band Management connection. If the qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is any value other than pvc(1), this object is non-applicable.

qbAtmInBandMgtVpi.name: qbAtmInBandMgtVpi
qbAtmInBandMgtVpi.description: If the value of qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is pvc(1), this is the VPI associated with this in-band management connection. If the value of qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is spvcInitiator(4), this object is target VPI. In all other cases, the value of this object is non-applicable.

qbAtmInBandMgtVci.name: qbAtmInBandMgtVci
qbAtmInBandMgtVci.description: If the value of qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is pvc(1), this is the VCI associated with this in-band management connection. If the value of qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is spvcInitiator(4), this object is target VCI. In all other cases, the value of this object is non-applicable.

qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind.name: qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind
qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind.description: This is the connection type associated with the in-band Management connection. The currently accepted types are pvc(1), spvcInitiator(4) and spvcTarget(5).

qbAtmInBandMgtTxTd.name: qbAtmInBandMgtTxTd
qbAtmInBandMgtTxTd.description: The Transmit traffic descriptor associated with this in-band management channel.

qbAtmInBandMgtRxTd.name: qbAtmInBandMgtRxTd
qbAtmInBandMgtRxTd.description: The Receive traffic descriptor associated with this in-band management channel.

qbAtmInBandMgtTargetNsapAddr.name: qbAtmInBandMgtTargetNsapAddr
qbAtmInBandMgtTargetNsapAddr.description: If the value of qbAtmInBandMgtConnKind is spvcInitiator(4) this object represetns the Target NSAP Address of the connection. In all other cases, the value of this object is non-applicable.

qbAtmInBandMgtRowStatus.name: qbAtmInBandMgtRowStatus
qbAtmInBandMgtRowStatus.description: To create, or delete an Entry in this table. Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the corresponding row to be created. Setting this object to destroy(6) causes the corresponding row to be deleted. Note that -- currently-- only a single instance of a row can be created in this table.
